scanTrace(25.10)                                              scanTrace(25.10)

Name
       scanTrace  -  Records the total number of elements in the scan chain in
       the log file, and records the starting and ending scan  points  if  the
       -verbose option is used

Syntax
       scanTrace

       [-help]

       [-compLogic | -noCompLogic]

       [-lockup | -noLockup]

       [-verbose]

       Records the total number of elements in the scan chain in the log file,
       and  records the starting and ending scan points if the -verbose option
       is used. The scanReorder command automatically calls  scanTrace  inter-
       nally if you have not previously run scanTrace.

       Note:  If scan chains are specified by reading in a DEF file, the soft-
       ware does a native scan trace. The scan DEF file is stored in the data-
       base and, when the scanReorder command runs, the software  matches  the
       scans and honors the ordered sections.

Parameters
       -compLogic
              Traces through multiple input gate on the scan path.

       -noCompLogic
              Does  not  trace  through  multiple input gate on the scan path.
              This is the default setting.

       -lockup
              Specifies that the tracing detects lockup latches automatically.

              Note: If the lockup elements are flops  (non  scan  flip-flops),
              the  lockup  elements must be identified using the specifyLocku-
              pElement command prior to running scanTrace in its default mode.

       -noLockup
              Specifies that the tracing will not detect lockup elements. This
              is the default.

       -verbose
              Prints the information stored in the logv file, i.e starting and
              ending scan points, and the cell instance names  that  scanTrace
              determines  are  part  of  the scan chain. If scan chain tracing
              fails, use this parameter to see where the  scan  chain  tracing
              stops.

Command Order
       Use  this  command  after specifying scan chains using the specifyScan-
       Chain command.

Examples
       The following set of commands traces all scan chains defined by  speci-
       fyScanChian command:

       specifyScanChain chain0 -start BG_scan_in_1 -stop BG_scan_out_1

        specifyScanChain chain1 -start BG_scan_in_2 -stop BG_scan_out_2

        specifyScanChain chain2 -start BG_scan_in_3 -stop BG_scan_out_3

        scanTrace

